    "body" : "<p>the IDENT_OUTPUT did not do anything for me, and to give a complete answer that works with my jackson 2.2.3 jars:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static void main(String[] args) throws IOException {\n\nbyte[] jsonBytes = Files.readAllBytes(Paths.get(\"C:\\\\data\\\\testfiles\\\\single-line.json\"));\n\nObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();\n\nObject json = objectMapper.readValue( jsonBytes, Object.class );\n\nSystem.out.println( objectMapper.writerWithDefaultPrettyPrinter().writeValueAsString( json ) );\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 87714,
      "reputation" : 6493,
      "user_id" : 243104,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 63,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/7c287efb5a1e622ed05eb07587be88ab?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Graham Lea",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/243104/graham-lea"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1428632232,
    "creation_date" : 1428632232,
    "answer_id" : 29552251,
    "question_id" : 17617370,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>If you'd like to turn this on by default for ALL ObjectMapper instances in a process, here's a little hack that will set the default value of INDENT_OUTPUT to true:</p>\n\n<pre><code>val indentOutput = SerializationFeature.INDENT_OUTPUT\nval defaultStateField = indentOutput.getClass.getDeclaredField(\"_defaultState\")\ndefaultStateField.setAccessible(true)\ndefaultStateField.set(indentOutput, true)\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 1437036,
        "reputation" : 3061,
        "user_id" : 1358179,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/00cfd044a6131e69ec0d6bfa114622f3?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
        "display_name" : "Martin",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1358179/martin"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 3,
      "creation_date" : 1499781871,
      "post_id" : 30411180,
      "comment_id" : 77047544,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "It’s still possible (with Jackson 2.7.6) to use <code>new ObjectMapper().configure(SerializationFeature.INDENT_OUTPUT, true).writer().writeValueAsString(new HashMap&lt;String, Object&gt;());</code>. You just have to make sure to use the writer you get from the configured <code>ObjectMapper</code>."
    } ],
